m's second-ever Phillips 66 Big 12 Championship trophy Sunday night inside the T-Mobile Center.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/DM102251.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/DM102251.JPG"><media:title>Big 12 Champions</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/DM102251.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 8 Mar 2026 21:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58830</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Take Finale Against Columbia</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/baseball-mountaineers-take-finale-against-columbia</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/baseball-mountaineers-take-finale-against-columbia</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matt Ineich" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/8/GB700008.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 23 West Virginia University baseball team cruised to a 16-1 victory over Columbia, Sunday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark to take the series. The Mountaineers improve to 10-3 while the Lions fall to 2-7.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/GB700008.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/GB700008.jpg"><media:title>Matt Ineich</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/GB700008.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 8 Mar 2026 18:14:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58829</s:story_id></item><item><title>Tennis Drops Match to No. 47 Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/tennis-drops-match-to-no-47-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/tennis-drops-match-to-no-47-baylor</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Julie Bousseau" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/8/TennisvsBaylor-5.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team dropped a match to No. 47 Baylor on Sunday morning at the Mountaineer Tennis Courts.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/TennisvsBaylor-5.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/TennisvsBaylor-5.png"><media:title>Julie Bousseau</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/8/TennisvsBaylor-5.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 8 Mar 2026 15:38:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58828</s:story_id></item><item><title>Bracket Set For Phillips 66 Big 12 Men’s Basketball Tournament</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/mens-basketball-bracket-set-for-phillips-66-big-12-mens-basketball-tournament</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/8/mens-basketball-bracket-set-for-phillips-66-big-12-mens-basketball-tournament</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="T-Mobile Center" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/3/11/T-Mobile-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />The bracket is set for the Phillips 66 Big 12 Men's Basketball Tournament, held March 10-14 at T-Mobile Center in Kansas City. Arizona, who captured its first Big 12 men's basketball regular season title, is the top seed with a 16-2 record. The 2026 event marks the 26th time Kansas City has served as host.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/3/11/T-Mobile-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/3/11/T-Mobile-Main.jpg"><media:title>T-Mobile Center</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/3/11/T-Mobile-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 8 Mar 2026 11:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58827</s:story_id></item><item><title>Harrison’s Late Steal Sends West Virginia to Big 12 Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/womens-basketball-harrisons-late-steal-sends-west-virginia-to-big-12-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/womens-basketball-harrisons-late-steal-sends-west-virginia-to-big-12-championship</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Jordan Harrison" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/7/030726_Big_12_Tourney_Day_4_TL-53.jpg" /><br /><br />KANSAS CITY, Mo. – The West Virginia women's basketball team held on in a tense, back-and-forth fourth quarter at T-Mobile Center, outlasting Colorado 48–47 after a series of clutch plays on both ends of the floor inside the final minute.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;im